          <history-note id="DLM262172">The item relating to the Bay of Plenty Regional Constituency was <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, as from <amendment-date>1 July 1992</amendment-date>, by section 15(2) <amending-leg>Local Government Amendment Act (No 2) 1992</amending-leg> (1992 No 71) <amending-instruction>by inserting the expression <quote.in quote="1">4</quote.in></amending-instruction>.</history-note>
          <history-note id="DLM262173">Note <amended-provision>4</amended-provision> was <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, as from <amendment-date>1 July 1992</amendment-date>, by section 15(3) <amending-leg>Local Government Amendment Act (No 2) 1992</amending-leg> (1992 No 71).</history-note>
          <history-note id="DLM262174">Schedule <amended-provision>7</amended-provision> was <amending-operation>repealed</amending-operation>, as from <amendment-date>1 July 2003</amendment-date>, by section <amending-provision href="DLM174092">266</amending-provision> <amending-leg>Local Government Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 84). <emphasis style="italic">See</emphasis> <citation jurisdiction="nz">sections <extref href="DLM174200">273 to 314</extref> of that Act</citation> as to the savings and transitional provisions.</history-note>
        </history>
